        <heading>3052.  Limitation on right of surety to recover what he paid creditor</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 3052.  Limitation on right of surety to recover what he paid creditor
A surety may not recover from the principal obligor more than he paid to secure a discharge, but he may recover by subrogation such attorney's fees and interest as are owed with respect to the principal obligation.</p>
        </content>
